<item>
            <title>[LU-8260] osd_ldiskfs fiemap code wrong address space usage</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8260</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;osd_io code seems to be using struct fiemap_extent&apos;s fi_extents_start field directly even though it has __user qualifier.&lt;br/&gt;
We then pass this buffer straight into inode&apos;s fiemap method that does assume the pointer is userspace which is boind to break on some conigurations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to at least set ds to kernel_ds to have it working,&lt;br/&gt;
 or find some other wayst to call into fiemap code with kernelspace buffers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Offending functions are osd_fiemap_get() and osd_is_mapped()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
